label.value: retinal rod bipolar cell morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the bipolar cells that function in low light and transmit signals only through amacrine cells.

label.value: retinal cone bipolar cell morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the retinal bipolar cells that connect to both ganglion and amacrine cells.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of this cysteine homologue produced by the demethylation of methionine, an intermediate in the biosynthesis of l-cysteine from l-methionine via l-cystathionine.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the erectile protuberance at the tip of the mammary gland in which the mammary ducts terminate and from which milk can be secreted.

label.value: blood vessel elastic tissue morphology trait

value.value: Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the tissue that is found in the tunica media of the vessels wall and allows vessels to stretch.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in whole blood, serum, or plasma of the fat derivatives in which one fatty acid has been replaced by a phosphate group.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the smaller of the two sacs in the vestibule.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the larger of the two sacs in the vestibule.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the epithelial cells that line the interior of the nose.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the neurons in the olfactory epithelium that are activated by specific odorants.
The proportion or numbers of the cells that transmit signals from the photoreceptors to retinal amacrine and ganglion cells.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the lobes of the cerebellum during their formation and differentiation.
The distance between the surfaces of the innermost cortical layer of the cerebellum that contains granule cells.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the floor of the midbrain which extends from the substantia nigra to the level of the cerebral aqueduct.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the floor of the midbrain which extends from the substantia nigra to the level of the cerebral aqueduct.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the mesencephalic roof plate, including the caudal and rostral part of the midbrain roof.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the rostral part of the midbrain roof.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the rostral part of the midbrain roof.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the common canal connecting the primordial atrium and ventricle.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the caudal region of the brain during its formation and differentiation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the wall between the atria or ventricles of the heart.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology during formation and differentiation of the path through which blood exits the heart.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the pulmonary vessels and aorta in relation to the heart.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the degree or shape of the bend in the transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye that serves as the chief refractory structure.
The distance between the external and internal surfaces of the skin folds covering the front of the eyeball.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of fold of skin of the upper eyelid that partially covers the inner corner of the eye.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of phagocytic cells of the myeloid lineage that capture antigens in the periphery and then migrate to the lymphoid organs and secrete cytokines to initiate immune responses.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the organizing signaling center that forms at the boundary between the midbrain and hindbrain and plays an essential role in development of the midbrain and anterior hindbrain.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the choroid.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color, or pattern of the blood vessel network of the conjunctiva.
The location or arrangement of the eye proper in relation to the eye socket.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the bony cavity that contains the eyeball or of any of the parts of the bones which form the cavity.
The distance from side to side of the bony cavity that contains the eyeball.
The distance from exterior to interior of the bony cavity that contains the eyeball or of any of the parts of the bones which form the cavity.

Correspondence in size, shape, and relative position of the bony cavities that contain the eyeball, or of any of the parts of the bones which form the cavity, on opposite sides of a dividing line or plane or about a center or axis.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the area in the retina where all of the axons of the ganglion cells exit the retina to form the optic nerve.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the area in the retina where all of the axons of the ganglion cells exit the retina to form the optic nerve.
The proportion or number of fibers in the optic nerve.
The proportion or number of cells in the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the morphology or physiology of the iris (the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye) during its formation and differentiation.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the adjustable membrane, composed of the stroma and pigmented epithelium, located just in front of the crystalline lens within the eye.
The proportion or number of cells in the lamellated connective tissue of the iris.
The proportion or number of pupils in one iris, each with sphincter muscle.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the blood vessels of the choroid.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the pupil within the eye.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the transparent structure of the eye responsible for focusing light rays.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the thickened peripheral margin of the vitreous membrane of the cornea.
The ability to open the eyelids.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the papillae that contain taste buds, including the fungiform, foliate, and circumvallate papillae.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the shape, structure, color or pattern of the mushroom-shaped papillae, which have a single taste bud at the tip, located mostly on the dorsal anterior portion of the tongue.
